This paper deals with the verification of population protocols, which are a formal model of sensor networks. The paper specifically focuses on immediate observation (IO) population protocols, which were introduced and studied in a previous paper. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), followed by cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves computational complexity and algorithms, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.PL (Programming Languages).
